name: Take it EC
description:
This piece is based on my mantra: to keep things simple... or easy.
Life is simple.  Do what you love, do your best, and forget the stress. To Take it EC is natural, beautiful, and powerful.
This necklace is make from copper plate, thunder glass, and sterling silver chain.
Please specify chain length upon purchase.

name: Ground and Purify
description:
Sterling and fine silver wrapped ring with Amber, Citrine, Moss Agate, and Tigers Eye.

About Amber:
Amber works on the body to heal and purify it, dissolving blockages and clearing chakras. It absorbs negative energy. As it is associated with the Solar Plexus chakra, Amber assists on helping one to be empowered, to overcome their fears and to instill courage and faith. It has a soothing, calming energy which can alleviate anxiety and stress, and help you to sleep.

Source: http://www.ascendedearth.com

name: Indigo Healing
description:
Rare Indigo Kyanite wrapped in sterling and fine silver with Moonstone, Rose Quartz, Jade, and Blue Topaz.

About Indigo Kyanite:
Indigo stimulates the Pineal Gland, or 3rd Eye Chakra, which enables psychic abilities to manifest, such as Clairvoyance and Clairaudience. It also helps one to communicate with Higher Beings from other realms. Kyanite also works energetically to clear and align all chakras, and can create new energy pathways, clearing old blockages and habitual patterns, allowing new and higher frequencies to enter the body. This is especially helpful if one is healing from trauma or surgery, or is stuck in an unhealthy pattern that they would like to break.

Source: www.ascendedearth.com

name: Cecropia Cuff
description:
The inspiration for this cuff came from the Cecropia Ring design I created earlier this year. 
The focal point of the bracelet consists of turquoise, malachite, and a large piece of smooth beach glass I found in the Virgin Islands. The surrounding beads include peach coral, rose quarts and amazonite from Russian (green) and Peru (blue). 
This bracelet is made from Sterling silver wire.

Cecropia Ring is available upon request. Please specify your ring size upon order.

*This cuff is designed to hug a small wrist comfortably. 

Have a question? Feel free to contact me via email.

name: Green Howlite Necklace
description:
Green howlite with yellow jade accent beads and a copper clasp.

Howlite is recognized for its calming abilities and is also a great alternative to similar stones that are being overmined. Turquoise and lapis for example are sacred to many cultures; yet global consumption has caused a dwindling supply. Substituting howlite is not only beautiful- but kind.

name: The Coca-Cola Cuff
description:
This cuff was inspired by a great find! Walking along the beach in the Virgin Islands I found a piece of beach glass which was originally from an old glass Coca-cola bottle. 
Framed in copper, the cuff is adorned with yellow and green turquoise as well as Czech glass and a rich patina finish. An absolute original!

This cuff is meant to be snug on the wrist. Upon purchase please give me the measurement of your wrist and I will make sure to resize it for you if necessary, free of charge.

name: Multi Faceted Opalite
description:
Multi faceted opalite necklace

Opalite or Sea Opal is milky, luminous, and slightly translucent. People will stop and ask "what the heck IS that?" Well its opalite glass! With every angle the opalite refracts different shades and colors ranging from whites and light blues to fiery reds, oranges, and yellows.

Blue Aventurine:
This stone is of the Third Eye or 6th Chakra which supports self-discipline, inner strength and over all emotional maturity while enhancing intuitive capabilities. Physically it promotes healthy blood, circulation, respiration, and hormonal balance.

Helps in opening new doors in the world of opportunities and utilizing them to the maximum by enhancing the creativity of a person while promoting general well being. It's especially great for meditation.

An interesting note about Chevron Amethyst:
"I had a dream...a man told me that these were very good for "grief", and for "letting go". Other things the chevron amethyst is known for is aura cleansing. By placing the amethyst on the individual chakras, it helps to release built up energy and blocks. The chevron amethyst relates to the 3rd eye or 6th chakra, and psychism. It is known to help people with visions, and it is also used for journeying, and self exploration and self discovery. Chevron amethyst combines the strengthening and enhancing qualities of quartz with the stress relieving qualities of amethyst. It is used to help one to beat addiction, so can be a great aid in recovery & sobriety. When carried upon ones person it acts to repel negativity from others by increasing the intensity of the wearers aura. Chevron amethyst is a stone of cooperation, healing, meditation, and stress relief. If you keep a piece of chevron amethyst by your bedside, it is said you will have peaceful and insightful dreams."
-Grandpa's General Store
